Question Text: When APs are placed at different geographic locations, they can all be interconnected by a switched infrastructure. The 802.11 standard calls this an extended service set (ESS).
LLM Explanation: The statement is true. When access points (APs) are placed at different geographic locations, they can be interconnected by a switched infrastructure to form an extended service set (ESS). An ESS is a set of one or more interconnected basic service sets (BSSs) and integrated local area networks (LANs) that appear as a single BSS to the logical link control layer at any station associated with one of those BSSs. This allows users to roam between APs while maintaining a seamless connection.
URLs: ['CWNA Certified Wireless Network Administrator Study Guide, 5th Edition by David D. Coleman and David A. Westcott', '802.11 Wireless Networks: The Definitive Guide, 2nd Edition by Matthew S. Gast', 'https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/wireless/controller/8-5/config-guide/b_cg85/b_cg85_chapter_01101.html']

Question Text: A lightweight access point in which one of the following architectures participate?
Choices:
a. Light-MAC
b. Tunnel-MAC
c. Big-MAC
d. Split-MAC
LLM Explanation: A lightweight access point participates in a split-MAC architecture. In this architecture, some of the MAC layer functionalities are handled by the access point itself, while others are handled by a central wireless LAN controller (WLC). This allows for centralized management and configuration of the wireless network.
URLs: ['CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Volume 1 by Wendell Odom', 'https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/wireless/controller/technotes/8-3/b_Lightweight_Access_Point_FAQ.html']

Question Text: Which of the following controller ports is used to connect to a peer controller for high availability (HA) operation?
Choices:
a. Service port
b. Distribution system port
c. Redundancy port
d. Console port
LLM Explanation: The redundancy port on a wireless LAN controller is used to connect to a peer controller for high availability (HA) operation. This dedicated port allows the active and standby controllers to synchronize their configurations and maintain a heartbeat. If the active controller fails, the standby controller connected via the redundancy port takes over to minimize downtime.
URLs: ['Cisco Wireless LAN Controller Configuration Guide, Release 8.10 - High Availability', 'CCNA Wireless (200-355) Official Cert Guide, Chapter 6: Understanding Wireless LAN Controllers']

Question Text: Which of the following wireless security tools is used to protect the integrity of data in a wireless frame?
Choices:
a. MIC
b. WIPS
c. WEP
d. EAP
LLM Explanation: MIC (Message Integrity Check) is a wireless security tool used to protect the integrity of data in a wireless frame. It is a checksum calculated over the data payload and header fields of a wireless frame, appended to the frame before encryption. The receiving device recalculates the MIC and compares it to the received MIC to ensure the frame was not altered in transit.
URLs: ['CWNA Certified Wireless Network Administrator Study Guide by David D. Coleman and David A. Westcott', '802.11 Wireless Networks: The Definitive Guide by Matthew S. Gast']

Question Text: Wi-Fi is based on ________________ IEEE standards.
LLM Explanation: Wi-Fi is based on the IEEE 802.11 standards. The 802.11 standards define the protocols and specifications for implementing wireless local area network (WLAN) communication in various frequency bands, such as 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz. The other IEEE standards mentioned in the choices are not directly related to Wi-Fi: 802.2 is for Logical Link Control (LLC), 802.1 is for bridging and management, and 802.12 is for demand priority access method.
URLs: ['IEEE 802.11 Wireless Local Area Networks: The Working Group for WLAN Standards. (n.d.). Retrieved from https://www.ieee802.org/11/', "Gast, M. (2005). 802.11 Wireless Networks: The Definitive Guide, Second Edition. O'Reilly Media."]

Question Text: Which of the following bridges can be used to provide wireless connectivity to a non-wireless device?
Choices:
a. Wireless repeater
b. Workgroup bridge
c. Transparent bridge
d. Adaptive bridge
LLM Explanation: A workgroup bridge can be used to provide wireless connectivity to a device that does not have built-in wireless capability. It connects to the non-wireless device via Ethernet and then wirelessly bridges the traffic to a wireless access point, allowing the non-wireless device to participate in the wireless network.
URLs: ['CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Volume 1 by Wendell Odom', 'https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/collateral/wireless/aironet-1200-access-point/prod_brochure09186a00801f7d0b.html']

Question Text: Which controller interface type maps a WLAN to a VLAN?
Choices:
a. Management interface
b. Redundancy management
c. Virtual interface
d. Service port interface
e. Dynamic interface
LLM Explanation: A dynamic interface on a Cisco wireless LAN controller maps a WLAN to a VLAN. It is used to route between VLANs and handle dynamic VLAN assignments for wireless clients. The other interfaces mentioned, like management, redundancy, virtual, and service port, serve different purposes and do not directly map WLANs to VLANs.
URLs: ['Cisco Wireless LAN Controller Configuration Guide, Release 8.0 - Configuring Dynamic Interfaces: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/wireless/controller/8-0/configuration-guide/b_cg80/b_cg80_chapter_01000.html', 'CCNA Wireless 200-355 Official Cert Guide, Chapter 6: Understanding Wireless LAN Controller Features and Functions']

Question Text: Which is the most preferred and secure way of connecting to a WLC GUI to configure a new WLAN?
Choices:
a. SSH
b. HTTP
c. HTTPS
d. FTP
e. None of the above
LLM Explanation: HTTPS is the most preferred and secure way of connecting to a WLC GUI to configure a new WLAN. HTTPS provides encryption for the communication between the client and the WLC, ensuring the confidentiality and integrity of the configuration data. SSH is secure but is used for CLI access, not GUI. HTTP is insecure as it sends data in plain text. FTP is a file transfer protocol and not used for WLC configuration.
URLs: ['Cisco Wireless LAN Controller Configuration Guide, Release 8.10 - Configuring Security Solutions: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/wireless/controller/8-10/config-guide/b_cg810/configuring_security_solutions.html', 'Cisco Wireless LAN Controller Configuration Best Practices: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/wireless/4400-series-wireless-lan-controllers/107686-wlc-config-best-practice.html']

Question Text: The maximum configurable number of WLANs on a controller is __________________.
LLM Explanation: The maximum configurable number of WLANs on a Cisco wireless LAN controller is 512. This allows for a large number of separate wireless networks to be configured and managed by a single controller device.
URLs: ['Cisco Wireless LAN Controller Configuration Guide, Release 8.10 - https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/wireless/controller/8-10/config-guide/b_cg810/b_cg810_chapter_01001.html']

Question Text: Which of the following IEEE 802.11 Wi-Fi standards use the 5 GHz band? (Choose all that apply)
LLM Explanation: The IEEE 802.11 Wi-Fi standards that use the 5 GHz band are: - 802.11a: The first Wi-Fi standard to use 5 GHz, providing up to 54 Mbps. - 802.11n: Operates on both 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz bands, offering speeds up to 600 Mbps. - 802.11ac: Operates exclusively on the 5 GHz band, with speeds up to 6.9 Gbps. - 802.11ax (Wi-Fi 6): The latest standard, operating on both 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz, with speeds up to 9.6 Gbps. The other standards listed (802.11, 802.11b, and 802.11g) operate only on the 2.4 GHz band.
URLs: ['IEEE 802.11 Wireless LAN Standards: https://www.electronics-notes.com/articles/connectivity/wifi-ieee-802-11/standards.php', 'Wi-Fi Alliance: Wi-Fi Generations: https://www.wi-fi.org/discover-wi-fi/wi-fi-generations']

Question Text: Wi-Fi commonly uses the 2.5GHz and __________________ GHz bands.
LLM Explanation: Wi-Fi commonly uses the 2.4GHz and 5GHz frequency bands. The 2.4GHz band is more widely supported by devices but is more prone to interference, while the 5GHz band offers higher speeds and less interference but has shorter range.

Question Text: Choose the term that best describes a Cisco wireless access point that operates in a standalone, independent manner.
Choices:
a. Standalone Access point (AP)
b. Autonomous Access Point (AP)
c. Independent Access Point (AP)
d. Cisco Access Point (AP)
LLM Explanation: The term that best describes a Cisco wireless access point operating in a standalone, independent manner is Autonomous Access Point (AP). An autonomous AP has all the configuration settings and wireless capabilities built into the individual unit itself, allowing it to function independently without relying on a centralized wireless LAN controller.
URLs: ['Cisco Press CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Chapter 27: Wireless Architectures', 'https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/wireless/access-points/index.html']

Question Text: You are creating a new WLAN with the controller GUI, which of the following parameters are necessary? (Choose two)
Choices:
a. VLAN number
b. SSID
c. Interface
d. BSSID
e. IP subnet
LLM Explanation: When creating a new WLAN with the controller GUI, the two necessary parameters are:a. VLAN number - This specifies the VLAN to which the WLAN should be mapped. Each WLAN needs to be associated with a VLAN for client traffic segmentation.  b. SSID (Service Set Identifier) - This is the network name that will be broadcasted to clients. It uniquely identifies the WLAN.The other options are not mandatory:c. Interface is not required during WLAN creation.d. BSSID (Basic Service Set Identifier) is automatically generated based on the access point's MAC address.e. IP subnet is not a direct parameter in WLAN configuration.
URLs: ['CCNA Wireless 200-355 Official Cert Guide, Chapter 6: Understanding a Basic Cisco Wireless LAN Controller Configuration', 'https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/wireless/controller/8-5/config-guide/b_cg85/wlan_interfaces.html']
SM - Description: VLAN is not necessary, since it is already associated with the interface. Interface is what you specify
Effect - Description of effects: Just not knowing beforehand what the require parameters are

Question Text: Which one of the following is a wireless encryption method that is not recommended for use due to vulnerability issues?
Choices:
a. Advanced Encryption Standard (AES)
b. Wi-Fi Protected Access (WPA)
c. Wired Equivalent Privacy (WEP)
d. Extensible Authentication Protocol (EAP)
LLM Explanation: Wired Equivalent Privacy (WEP) is a wireless encryption method that is not recommended for use due to known vulnerabilities. WEP uses a static key shared between devices, making it susceptible to key recovery attacks. Attackers can capture enough data packets to crack the encryption key, compromising the security of the wireless network. WEP has been superseded by more secure protocols like WPA, WPA2, and WPA3 that use stronger encryption algorithms and dynamic keys.
URLs: ['CISCO Press - CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Chapter 11: Wireless LANs', 'IEEE 802.11 Wireless LAN Standard', 'NIST Special Publication 800-48 Rev. 1 - Guide to Securing Legacy IEEE 802.11 Wireless Networks']

Question Text: Which of the following IEEE 802.11 Wi-Fi standards use the 2.4 GHz band? (Choose all that apply)
LLM Explanation: The IEEE 802.11 Wi-Fi standards that use the 2.4 GHz band are:- 802.11: The original Wi-Fi standard, which operates in the 2.4 GHz band.- 802.11b: Operates in the 2.4 GHz band and provides a maximum data rate of 11 Mbps.- 802.11g: Operates in the 2.4 GHz band and provides a maximum data rate of 54 Mbps.- 802.11n: Can operate in both the 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz bands, providing improved range and speed compared to previous standards.- 802.11ax (Wi-Fi 6): The latest Wi-Fi standard, which can operate in both the 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz bands, offering improved efficiency, capacity, and performance.802.11a and 802.11ac operate exclusively in the 5 GHz band.
